The SA National Defence Force (SANDF) confirmed that a massive fire, which broke out at the Waterkloof Air Force Base in Pretoria on Sunday evening after a fuel pump burst, has been extinguished. The SANDF's spokesperson, Brigadier-General Mongezi Kweta, said the fire started on the bulk fuel storage facility following a suspected leakage from a burst pump late on Sunday afternoon. While Kweta said the SANDF had launched an investigation into the cause of the fire, he added that it had no reason to suspect any foul play at this stage. Fire at Waterkloof Airforce base. Seems to be a fire at the fuel tanks. @crimeairnetwork @Abramjee @crimewatch202 @CrimeStop_RSA pic.twitter.com/8V4HpTKSlb    News24 was told that the SA Air Force Chief, Lieutenant-General Wiseman Mbambo, was on the scene to assess the damage. "For now, I can confirm that military firefighters are busy at the scene. The fire has been contained. We are waiting for more details from officers on the scene," said Kweta on Sunday night. Reports of a fire at the Waterkloof Airbase in Pretoria. pic.twitter.com/0BOgFSEVWI 